<item>
            <title>[FLUME-3031] sequence source should reset its counter for event body on channel exception</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLUME-3031</link>
                <project id="12311321" key="FLUME">Flume</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;SequenceGeneratorSource uses a counter to construct the body of the generated Events which counter is not reseted when writing event to channel failed. This can lead to a situation that the total number of unique events at destination (if deduplication relies on msg body) is bigger than the totalEvents configuration parameter due to the retries.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fix should make sure that number of events at destination after filtering out the duplicates is equal to the configured value.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
